Implement optional network connectivity testing for the check command.

## Feature Description
When `--test-connectivity` flag is provided, actually test that proxies are reachable:

```bash
rust_proxy check --test-connectivity
```

## Implementation

### Connection Test Logic
```rust
async fn test_proxy_connectivity(proxy: &ProxyDef, timeout_ms: u64) -> ConnectivityResult {
    let timeout = Duration::from_millis(timeout_ms);
    let start = Instant::now();

    // 1. Resolve proxy host
    let addrs = match tokio::net::lookup_host(&proxy.url_host_port()).await {
        Ok(addrs) => addrs.collect::<Vec<_>>(),
        Err(e) => return ConnectivityResult::DnsFailure(e.to_string()),
    };

    // 2. TCP connect
    let stream = match tokio::time::timeout(timeout, TcpStream::connect(&addrs[0])).await {
        Ok(Ok(s)) => s,
        Ok(Err(e)) => return ConnectivityResult::ConnectFailure(e.to_string()),
        Err(_) => return ConnectivityResult::Timeout,
    };

    // 3. Send CONNECT request (to httpbin or configurable endpoint)
    // ... send CONNECT httpbin.org:443 HTTP/1.1 ...

    ConnectivityResult::Success {
        latency_ms: start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64,
    }
}

enum ConnectivityResult {
    Success { latency_ms: u64 },
    DnsFailure(String),
    ConnectFailure(String),
    AuthFailure(String),
    Timeout,
}
```

### Output Format
```
Proxies (2 defined):
✓ mesh-us: http://us-wa.proxymesh.com:31280 (auth: env vars)
  → Connectivity: ✓ reachable (45ms)
✗ mesh-eu: http://eu.proxymesh.com:31280 (auth: env vars)
  → Connectivity: ✗ connection refused
```

### JSON Output
```json
{
  "id": "mesh-us",
  "url": "http://us-wa.proxymesh.com:31280",
  "connectivity": {
    "status": "success",
    "latency_ms": 45
  }
}
```

## Considerations
- This is optional and slower (network I/O)
- Should have reasonable timeout (5 seconds default)
- Should run connectivity tests in parallel for multiple proxies
- Auth failures vs connection failures should be distinguished

